<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Basic Authentication Demo</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            text-align: left;
        }
        h1, h2, p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Welcome to the Basic Authentication Demo</h1>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <p>Explore the following features:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>User Registration</li>
        <li>User Login</li>
        <li>Session Management</li>
        <li>Password Hashing</li>
        <li>Protected Routes</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Routes</h2>
    <p>Discover the different routes:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>/ (Homepage)</li>
        <li>/register</li>
        <li>/login</li>
        <li>/secret1</li>
        <li>/secret2</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <p>Follow these steps to interact with the app:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>Visit the homepage to see the welcome message.</li>
        <li>Navigate to /register to create a new account.</li>
        <li>Login at /login with your registered credentials.</li>
        <li>Access protected routes (/secret1 and /secret2) when logged in.</li>
        <li>Logout using /logout to end your session.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Important Notes</h2>
    <p>Make sure MongoDB is running locally on port 27017 or update the connection string in index.js. This demo is for educational purposes and additional security measures are advised for production.</p>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> This demo does not include comprehensive error handling. In a real-world application, it is crucial to implement robust error handling to enhance the app's reliability and security.</p>

    <p>Feel free to explore and modify the code to suit your needs!</p>

</body>
</html>
